31
00:03:06,054 --> 00:03:08,033
In my hypothesis,

32
00:03:08,034 --> 00:03:11,394
I realized that there might be an error.

33
00:03:15,274 --> 00:03:17,063
There is no such thing as
true love for a woman,

34
00:03:17,064 --> 00:03:19,694
are you talking about that?

35
00:03:20,904 --> 00:03:22,403
Yes.

36
00:03:22,404 --> 00:03:25,984
That means it will really turn
this experiment upside down.

37
00:03:26,004 --> 00:03:27,753
Then, what are we going to do now?

38
00:03:27,754 --> 00:03:30,893
I already set aside the budget
to invest in your experiment,

39
00:03:30,894 --> 00:03:32,803
we also decided on the direction
marketing would take.

40
00:03:32,804 --> 00:03:38,063
I'll do my utmost to help you with marketing from
the point of view of a psychologist, however

41
00:03:38,064 --> 00:03:41,494
for now, I will postpone this experiment.

42
00:03:43,974 --> 00:03:47,204
<i>This is really just a
small possibility, but</i>

43
00:03:47,224 --> 00:03:51,373
<i>Soo Hyun may say he is going
to cancel the experiment.</i>

44
00:03:51,374 --> 00:03:52,893
What?

45
00:03:52,894 --> 00:03:55,183
Do you know how much we
spent on this experiment?

46
00:03:55,184 --> 00:03:57,703
I'm sorry, Chairman.

47
00:03:57,704 --> 00:04:01,823
But if that happens, Soo Hyun has
committed a breach of contract anyway.

48
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:05,123
Let's say that the company will
compensate for the damages.

49
00:04:05,124 --> 00:04:08,893
What do you think about
scolding Soo Hyun separately?

50
00:04:08,894 --> 00:04:12,973
For example, like giving him a penalty.

51
00:04:12,974 --> 00:04:14,744
A penalty?

52
00:04:19,274 --> 00:04:22,623
Exactly what kind of plan did you come up with?
What kind of favor did you ask of the Chairman?

53
00:04:22,624 --> 00:04:23,753
What do you mean?

54
00:04:23,754 --> 00:04:28,974
All I was told was to give you psychological
counseling because you had a problem.

55
00:04:30,024 --> 00:04:34,444
That's my seat. Since you're the client,
please sit on the opposite side.

56
00:04:47,324 --> 00:04:50,274
How do you feel these days?

57
00:04:50,284 --> 00:04:52,204
Just so-so.

58
00:04:52,884 --> 00:04:53,884
Ah right!

59
00:04:53,885 --> 00:04:57,083
An interesting thing happened to me.
I'm a psychological counselor, but

60
00:04:57,084 --> 00:04:59,483
